<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-06T17:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-06T17:40:00-05:00" n="308" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d308">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1288.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Sullivan</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-06T18:00:00-04:40">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 6, 1914, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Government preparing for election on 7th and 8th and claims will proceed
                            without inconvenience in eight of twelve provinces. Minister for Foreign
                            Affairs says that supplementary election will be held when insurrection
                            is subdued. I have made preparations for observation of elections.
                            Government asserts it can not be held responsible for non-participation
                            in the elections by opposing elements who have preferred to seek success
                            by force of arms.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>